=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Overviews_Operators_ex51 ===

DESCRIPTION: A neutral pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 1002 Hz, featuring instant attack and dynamic envelope, with evolving spectral movement, energy distribution is front_heavy, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: instant
  brightness: neutral
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: evolving
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: front_heavy

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 1002.1316
  harmonic_decay_rate: -3.7907
  harmonic_regularity: 0.0575
  pitch_clarity: 163.9248
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -2.3399
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Operators Example 51
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Overviews/Operators.html
// Tags: Operators, Overviews
// ---
// --- Example 51 ---
(
{
    var a;
    a = Line.ar(-2, 2, 0.01);
    a.excess
}.plot
)

{ FSinOsc.ar(1000).excess(Line.kr(0,1,8)) }.play;
